FBIS3-52636 "drnes004_p_94003" FBIS-NES-94-004 Document Type:Daily Report 6 Jan 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Iranian Embassy Tries to Broker Cease-Fire LD0601114994 Tehran IRNA in English 1538 GMT 5 Jan 94 LD0601114994 Tehran IRNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Kabul, Jan. 5, IRNA -- Iranian Embassy in Kabul has launched serious efforts to broker a cease-fire among the Afghan rival factions, Iran's ambassador to Kabul, Gholamreza Haddadi, told reporters here Wednesday. Haddadi stated that as far as negotiations with different Afghan rival factions are concerned, they seem to be ready to accept mediation for establishment of a cease-fire. "Afghan rival factions believe that none of the country's political parties should be excluded from the future government of Afghanistan," Haddadi added.
